 {"id":"688e5fc4-794e-4b41-8f52-45089b842f9f","type":"decide","date":"2026-07-10T04:20:10.972Z","decision":"Review slot + effort knob (decision 0021, P16/P17): models map defaults to the all-Claude role split — session model orchestrates, opus reviews (reviewing specialists, fresh-eyes, plan-checker), sonnet implements, haiku extracts — every slot editable per repo (string | null | {model,effort} | {kind:cli}); null review falls back to generation","rationale":"Owner adopted the Fable/Opus/Sonnet/GPT role split as default: the model that reviews should not be the model that implemented; editability keeps it honest for users with only one subscription","alternatives":null,"scope":"repo","source":"decision doc 0021","confidence":null}
 {"id":"29b7f7bb-feb0-44f3-997b-94fe3584ab7a","type":"decide","date":"2026-07-10T04:44:19.721Z","decision":"External-dispatch field refinements (from the codex-first pattern): result via -o file (never parse JSONL), stderr suppressed by default, rescue prefers codex exec resume --last with the failing verify output (max 2 rounds then BLOCKED), session-tool/MCP/secrets/destructive cells never route to cli executors, workspace-write only — no --yolo default","rationale":"A practitioner skill running the same Claude-specs/Codex-implements split surfaced the operational edges bee's 0019 protocol lacked: cheap context-preserving retries, output hygiene, and tool-dependency dispatch guards","alternatives":null,"scope":"repo","source":"owner-shared codex-first skill, 2026-07-10","confidence":null}
 {"id":"20784de8-d2ed-47d1-b332-aa5a635ada68","type":"decide","date":"2026-07-10T05:04:10.003Z","decision":"Evolving loop design settled (P18): dogfood repos stay zero-effort (digest is a compounding side effect); bee-evolving runs only in the bee repo, on demand; improvements go through the Iron Law (failing pressure test first); two human gates (what to fix, approve push) — push never auto","rationale":"Owner wants bee to learn from real anphabe-gogl usage and ship improvements to GitHub; separation keeps project decisions and bee-design decisions in different sessions, and gated push keeps self-modification under the same discipline bee imposes on everything else","alternatives":null,"scope":"repo","source":"owner discussion 2026-07-10","confidence":null}
 {"id":"ff26725d-bbf8-49b5-99cf-ed8edbc26b0d","type":"decide","date":"2026-07-10T05:22:41.330Z","decision":"Iron Law binds skill edits with no mechanical-edit exemption: a cell that edits any SKILL.md carries RED/GREEN pressure-test evidence, even when it only adds a numbered step invoking an already-verified command","rationale":"Owner chose (a) at Gate 2 of the evolving loop (P18). Carving an exemption into the one law bee uses to protect itself from its own edits would be the first crack; bee-writing-skills already predicts the rationalization ('it is just one step'). Cost is bounded — a pressure scenario per skill edit — and the loop being built here is precisely the machinery that will edit skills at scale","alternatives":"Mechanical-edit exemption for step-only additions that introduce no rule, discipline, or refusal (rejected by owner)","scope":"repo","source":"user","confidence":5}
 {"id":"8cd4c84e-0ed6-422e-9213-3eaa085c8a37","type":"supersede","date":"2026-07-10T05:37:32.464Z","supersedes":"20784de8-d2ed-47d1-b332-aa5a635ada68","decision":"Evolving loop design (P18, v2): (D1) dogfood repos stay zero-effort — digest is a compounding side effect; (D2 REVISED) the digest is an ALLOWLIST of structured fields — kind, layer, source, title, first_seen, pain — and carries NO free detail/text field, because measurement showed friction prose routinely names functions, files and config keys that no code-block strip or secret regex removes; (D2b) the CONSUMER revalidates and datamarks every foreign digest entry before it can enter a prompt, and every source path is realpath-contained; (D3) bee-evolving runs only in the bee repo, on demand; (D4) improvements go through the Iron Law (failing pressure test first, edits included); (D5) two human gates (what to fix, approve push) — push never auto","rationale":"Validating slice A measured the real corpus across 5 bee repos and found the original D2 unenforceable: friction detail text is unfenced prose containing identifiers (readBacklogCounts, COMMAND_KEYS, approved_gates.shape, internal call graphs), which passes code-block stripping, passes the secret and injection regexes, and fits inside the 600-char cap. The plan had already shrunk D2 in prose without superseding it, violating its own prohibition. Owner chose the allowlist over a weakened promise: drop free text entirely rather than advertise a guarantee the pipeline cannot keep. D2b is added because the security panel showed the redaction boundary sat at the producer while bee-evolving — the consumer — is the party that edits its own source from foreign files; write-time scanning protects the wrong party, and a symlink under a foreign .bee/ defeats a string-prefix scope check"}
 {"id":"c874a4b3-7f4e-4cca-914e-dab9375ed326","type":"decide","date":"2026-07-10T07:19:48.895Z","decision":"Realpath containment is the only read-scope guard","rationale":"Every filesystem read routes through resolveInScope(root, relPath) which path.resolve-normalizes then fs.realpath-validates against the repo root. fs.realpath rejects symlink escapes; a symlinked .bee/cells/evil.json pointing outside the repo is warned and never read. This is a read-scope invariant, not a sandbox. Bypassing it with fs.promises or named imports creates a silent escape hatch and must be prevented by source-level drift testing.","alternatives":null,"scope":"repo","source":"user","confidence":null}
 {"id":"25687451-f1dd-449c-af47-96fff220a0d5","type":"decide","date":"2026-07-10T07:19:55.244Z","decision":"Digest is an allowlist snapshot with no free-text fields","rationale":"Each digest entry carries exactly six fields: kind, layer, source, title, first_seen, pain. No detail/text/outcome/deviations field. This removes surface cross-file dependencies from reachable data. A friction entry naming readBacklogCounts and COMMAND_KEYS leaves neither string in digest bytes. ENTRY_FIELDS, KIND_ALIASES, and DROP_REASONS are single-sourced and drift-tested to prevent accidental divergence. Import these constants rather than hardcoding copies in multiple modules.","alternatives":null,"scope":"repo","source":"user","confidence":null}
 {"id":"c1c65f42-b11b-4a57-9f7b-bedc565f2a79","type":"decide","date":"2026-07-10T07:20:00.571Z","decision":"Foreign digest consumer revalidation: re-scan, datamark, allowlist enforcement","rationale":"The producing repo's write-time scan does not protect the consumer. A hand-edited or hostile digest is just JSON on disk. For every foreign entry: resolve the path and reject symlink escapes by realpath; re-run SECRET_CONTENT_PATTERNS and INJECTION_PATTERNS dropping violators; wrap surviving titles in datamark() before they can enter a prompt (this prevents injection attacks); enforce ENTRY_FIELDS allowlist, never merging extra fields through. A missing or corrupt digest is warned and skipped, never thrown.","alternatives":null,"scope":"repo","source":"user","confidence":null}
 {"id":"c45d0fb3-dfd4-482f-a090-445ce9d32126","type":"decide","date":"2026-07-10T07:45:17.724Z","decision":"A frozen assertion that encodes a defect is unfrozen by the planner/orchestrator, never by the worker: test_lib.mjs:1833 asserted a foreign entry's source survives mergeDigests raw ('src'), which IS the P1-1 vulnerability. Updating it to require datamarking is a strengthening, not a weakening, and the worker correctly returned [BLOCKED] rather than rewrite it","rationale":"Cell evolving-3 wrote both the consumer-side boundary and the test that accepted its own gap; 93 green assertions therefore proved conformance to a wrong spec, not safety. Two opus reviewers reading the code missed that the suite blessed the defect — it surfaced only when a worker tried to fix the bug and the suite refused. The frozen-assertion rule must keep its escape hatch (worker STOPS and quotes the assertion) or the first defect encoded in a test becomes permanent","alternatives":"Let the worker silently update the assertion (rejected: indistinguishable from weakening a test to make a change pass). Keep the assertion and drop the fix (rejected: ships the P1)","scope":"repo","source":"user","confidence":5}
 {"id":"b8fe5c81-67d4-4359-b189-0c52fe685558","type":"decide","date":"2026-07-10T08:26:01.458Z","decision":"Second narrow unfreeze (evolving-7): the ENTRY_FIELDS source-literal grep in test_lib.mjs:1421-1422 is deleted; the value-lock, the no-free-text check, and the SCHEMA_VERSION/DROP_REASONS literal pins all stay. A drift guard that regex-matches a module's own source pins SYNTAX, not behavior — and here the pinned syntax (a bare name array) was the defect itself, blocking the structural fix that makes forgetting a field impossible","rationale":"Third occurrence of one defect class: mergeDigests neutralized only the fields someone remembered. The fix replaces ENTRY_FIELDS with ENTRY_FIELD_SPEC (field -> validator) and derives the name list from it, so an unspecced field cannot exist. The frozen grep demanded the literal array and thus forbade the fix. The repo already logged this exact anti-pattern against BACKLOG_STATUSES ('a value-lock, not a cross-file guard — regex-matching its own source guards nothing'), so this is a known, twice-seen failure mode, and the second worker to hit a defect-encoding assertion again correctly returned [BLOCKED] instead of rewriting it","alternatives":"Keep the grep and patch only first_seen (rejected: field-by-field patching is what failed in rounds 1 and 2). Let the worker delete the assertion itself (rejected: indistinguishable from weakening a test to pass)","scope":"repo","source":"user","confidence":5}
 {"id":"7fb024e3-767c-4586-a754-7de1499c2590","type":"decide","date":"2026-07-10T08:42:01.813Z","decision":"Prefer an allowlist of structured fields over a blocklist filter whenever the data is human-authored prose: prose reliably embeds identifiers, and no strip or regex finds them. And place a redaction boundary at the party AT RISK, not the party producing the data — in a self-modifying or cross-trust pipeline, write-time validation protects the wrong party","rationale":"Two independent surprises in P18 that neither the plan, the advisor, nor the first validation pass predicted. (1) Measurement showed the code-block strip removed exactly zero characters from real friction prose, which named functions, files, and config keys in ordinary sentences; the honest fix was deleting the field, not sharpening the filter. (2) The producing repo's write-time scan guards that repo against its own workers. bee-evolving reads foreign digests to edit bee's own source, so bee is the party at risk and must revalidate at read time — found only by a security lens explicitly asked who is at risk","alternatives":"Sharpen the blocklist (rejected: measured no-op). Single write-time boundary (rejected: protects the producer, not the consumer)","scope":"repo","source":"user","confidence":5}
 {"id":"c75fed88-732d-4f4c-bdf3-fe2349f00a37","type":"decide","date":"2026-07-10T10:47:04.709Z","decision":"Gate 4 evolving-loop slice B: owner explicitly acknowledged merging with 2 open P1s (rank --json emits stripped key; normalizeTitle duplicates datamark cleaning) — both filed to backlog as fix-first candidates; review record review-slice-b.md","rationale":"Owner's explicit Gate 4 choice on 2026-07-10; both P1s are corroboration-promoted defense-in-depth gaps (code boundary intact per security review), concrete fixes recorded in backlog so nothing evaporates","alternatives":null,"scope":"repo","source":"user","confidence":null}
 {"id":"a3f8d2b2-265d-48d4-a499-d4c7369f923c","type":"decide","date":"2026-07-10T10:55:33.658Z","decision":"Build self-modifying skills at the strongest tier, but pressure-probe their gates with the weakest plausible model: evolving-10 was authored at ceiling while all four RED/GREEN scenarios ran against fresh haiku subagents — a refusal only the strong model produces is not a guardrail","rationale":"All four RED failures were plausible middle options invented by the weak model (patch-on-branch, standing pre-approval, runbook push); the GREEN pass only held because the skill forecloses each rationalization by name. Probe strength and build strength are independent dispatch decisions","alternatives":null,"scope":"repo","source":"user","confidence":9}
 {"id":"d02a6bc6-ba12-434f-8035-34bc4f90ad22","type":"decide","date":"2026-07-10T15:22:31.073Z","decision":"Lane scaling v2: ceremony now truly scales — docs lane (knowledge-only files: no gates/cells/reviewers, announce-then-do + capture); tiny/small merge Gates 2+3 into one shape+execution question with the reality check inline in planning (bee-validating not separately invoked, 0 validating subagents); tiny/small execute solo in-session (no swarm workers, cell discipline kept); review scales: tiny = self-review + done-report (no Gate 4 question), small = 1 correctness reviewer, standard = 4 core + learnings pair, high-risk = full wave + conditionals","rationale":"config-sample (a tiny sample-file task) burned ~9 subagent dispatches and 4 human stops because validating/swarming/reviewing had no lane conditions despite the 'lanes scale ceremony, never memory' principle. Owner confirmed all 4 design choices via structured Q&A: self-review for tiny, solo execution for tiny/small, 1 merged gate for tiny, dedicated docs lane. Knowledge machinery (decision log, capture stubs, spec sync) intentionally unchanged in every lane — it was never the bottleneck","alternatives":null,"scope":"repo","source":"user","confidence":null}
 {"id":"9749b660-f344-4183-8938-002cca18b629","type":"decide","date":"2026-07-10T15:33:07.875Z","decision":"config-sample.json lives at .bee/config-sample.json (owner instruction 2026-07-10), superseding the config-sample feature's root-location choice (D1) and cell config-sample-2's 'no .bee/config-sample.json' truth","rationale":"Owner wants the sample colocated with bee's runtime config directory. Content unchanged; no living doc referenced the root path","alternatives":null,"scope":"repo","source":"user","confidence":null}
 {"id":"9d9591ca-092e-4399-971d-7163e21f1bf2","type":"decide","date":"2026-07-10T16:39:18.032Z","decision":"External-executor finish contract (external-result-contract): a cli worker's last FILE act is writing .bee/workers/<cell-id>.result.json — outcome is exactly the four status tokens (the cli transport of the one worker contract) — and the orchestrator accepts by file, never by exit: missing/unparseable/invalid result = failed run into the rescue ladder. The prompt file at .bee/workers/<cell-id>.prompt.md IS the durable contract; resume rounds reference it and never re-pass dispatch-time flags (resume inherits sandbox/config). Rejected from the repository-harness source: partial/needs_intake outcomes, schema-validator tooling, preemptive worktree-shim machinery (one conditional sentence only).","rationale":"Adapted from repository-harness SYMPHONY_SCOPE 4.4/4.6 after the codex-first refinements (29b7f7bb) left silent-death detection undefined. Field-proven same day: the feature's own review ran the protocol (codex reviewer, -o result, 2 resume rescues); an independent cross-model reviewer caught 5 real findings including two author self-contradictions. Acceptance rules ported without their machinery keep the harness lean.","alternatives":null,"scope":"repo","source":"user","confidence":9}
 {"id":"2ce745d8-6c00-4633-aea4-4dc466ff516e","type":"decide","date":"2026-07-10T17:57:35.951Z","decision":"Gate 4 learnings-pair-relocation: owner chose fix-then-close; both P1s (wave cap refill, 0021 tier drift) and the P3 fixed in cell -2, grep-verified, feature approved for close","rationale":"Owner decision 2026-07-11 via structured gate question; fixes are one-phrase gated_auto items verified by the cell verify chain (negative+positive greps, test_lib 124/0)","alternatives":null,"scope":"repo","source":"user","confidence":null}
 {"id":"aec38e11-b007-41a6-bc81-ba63c13184b0","type":"decide","date":"2026-07-10T17:59:28.508Z","decision":"Review wave composition (learnings-pair-relocation): standard lane = exactly 4 core reviewers, wave cap 6 (4 core + max 2 conditionals on the review slot); synthesis (dedupe, corroboration promotion, autofix_class, severity counts) is the orchestrator's OWN inline duty after ALL reviewers return — never a dispatched subagent; precedent flows planning bootstrap -> plan.md -> reviewers, no review-time learnings dispatch. Supersedes decision 0021's researcher=extraction/synthesizer=ceiling tier clause (those agents no longer exist); knowledge machinery unchanged in every lane.","rationale":"Owner-approved 2026-07-11: review-time precedent search only annotated findings after code existed (planning already owned the search per its bootstrap); the synthesizer subagent ran on the orchestrator's model so it added a dispatch, not a mind. -2 dispatches per standard/high-risk feature. Cap 7->6 was a reviewer-forced correction: a capacity constant derived from the old roster would have silently refilled the freed slots.","alternatives":"Literal relocation (add researcher step to planning, synthesis step to compounding) rejected as duplication - both already owned the duty. Keeping the pair rejected: 2 dispatches per feature for annotation-after-the-fact.","scope":"repo","source":"user","confidence":null}
 {"id":"94d69cf1-68ea-448a-934c-aa4d36474b59","type":"decide","date":"2026-07-11T03:25:33.228Z","decision":"Gate 4 skill-sync: owner approved merge after the fix wave closed all 9 code-confirmed P1s (02662bf hardening, 3d36b22 contract); UAT RUN item passed live (apply synced drifted bee-hive, recheck up_to_date with hash parity); 7 P2 hardening items filed to backlog non-blocking","rationale":"Owner decision 2026-07-11 via structured gate question; every fix red-first with recorded pre-fix failures, orchestrator goal-checked both cells in the session shell","alternatives":null,"scope":"repo","source":"user","confidence":null}
 {"id":"e7a54e78-7b6e-4294-8cb0-3c2952ca129f","type":"decide","date":"2026-07-11T03:28:13.753Z","decision":"skill-sync shipped policies (supplement D1-D5, all Gate-3/4-covered): production target is hard-coded os.homedir()/.claude/skills with NO override (tests isolate via spawned-process fake HOME/USERPROFILE); symlinked bee-* entries or inner symlinks = blocked_symlink, skipped loudly, never written/unlinked/deleted; absent tree = fresh install vs existing-unreadable = unknown = refuse; --force-downgrade only when all three versions resolve numeric AND the dry-run exposed the items it will mutate (forced_downgrade:true reported); skill plan items carry scope: installed|source; case-alias collisions = blocked_alias fail-closed; repoRoot-targetRoot overlap refuses pre-write","rationale":"Owner-approved through Gates 3/4 on 2026-07-11; each policy is enforced by red-first tests (232+ checks incl. a real case-insensitive /mnt/c run) after the review wave found 9 code-confirmed P1s","alternatives":null,"scope":"repo","source":"user","confidence":null}
+{"id":"ae745493-f1e1-4c81-a620-23c2a09d6fe3","type":"decide","date":"2026-07-11T05:53:11.756Z","decision":"Gate 3 model-tier-guard: auto-approved via gate bypass (standard lane, no hard-gate flag) — verdict READY WITH CONSTRAINTS after reality gate PASS, 7/7 feasibility rows PROVEN, 3 plan-check iterations + orchestrator-verified mechanical closure of the last cell-3 grep finding; constraints: cell-4 transaction blast radius noted, live-fire deny is orchestrator-owned at acceptance + Gate 4 UAT with reopen rule","rationale":"Owner enabled bee-bypass-gate; advisor consult at execution point satisfied inline (session model = configured advisor model fable); full report docs/history/model-tier-guard/reports/validation-slice1.md","alternatives":null,"scope":"repo","source":"user","confidence":null}
+{"id":"d50564fa-cc57-457a-8178-1e06b8a5b319","type":"decide","date":"2026-07-11T06:07:09.009Z","decision":"0023 — explicit-tier transport: every Agent/Task dispatch now carries an explicit tier (model param or [bee-tier: <tier>] marker); bare dispatches are denied by the new bee-model-guard PreToolUse hook. Amends only the transport clause of decision 0015 (omit-param alone no longer means ceiling — omit-param + marker does); the principle that the ceiling is the session model, never configured, stands unchanged. Written as docs/decisions/0023-explicit-tier-transport.md with a single Status amendment line added to 0015.","rationale":"Owner observed during a live session that tier_mix.ceilingShare=0.4 with 21 untiered cells — dispatches were silently inheriting the expensive session model because omitting the model param was ambiguous between deliberate ceiling and a forgotten tier. The model-tier-guard feature (cells 1-3, capped) built the hook, registration, and skill-doc wording; this cell records the decision and applies onboarding to vendor/wire it.","alternatives":null,"scope":"repo","source":"user","confidence":null}
